Margate SAPS spokesperson captain Gerald Mfeka says there is a safety concern as diggers are using equipment not intended for mining. JOHANNESBURG - KwaZulu-Natal police have been deployed to a village in Harding where thousands of people have converged in search of gold. It’s understood word spread over the weekend that the precious metal had been dug up in a rural village called KwaMachi. Police say people have been flocking to the area since Monday in the hope of cashing in. Margate SAPS spokesperson captain Gerald Mfeka says there is a safety concern as diggers are using equipment not intended for mining. “Police were deployed in the area for the sake of the safety of the people who are digging for gold.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)